info.senderName: NWS Jacksonville (Northeast Florida and Southeast Georgia)
info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 11 at 5:06PM EST by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Gilchrist, western Alachua, northwestern Marion, southwestern Columbia and southeastern Suwannee Counties through 545 PM EST... At 506 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles west of Fowlers Bluff to 7 miles southeast of Chiefland to 8 miles south of Bronson to 12 miles west of Rainbow Lakes Estates. Movement was northeast at 35 mph. HAZARD...Winds around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Trenton, Bell, Ichetucknee Spring, Alachua, High Springs, Archer, Fort White, Newberry, Branford and La Crosse. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
